Sure, they're not going away anytime soon.  But the question Windows ISVs face 
is not just whether they can get additional users by covering those platforms,
the question is whether getting those additional users is worth the cost
of getting them.  For some products on some platforms, the answer is yes.
However, for many products, and many platforms, the answer is no.
 
